.TH "vpif_buffer_queue_setup" 9 "vpif_buffer_queue_setup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vpif_buffer_queue_setup \- Callback function for buffer setup.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vpif_buffer_queue_setup
.BI "(struct vb2_queue *vq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *nbuffers "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *nplanes "  ","
.BI "unsigned int sizes[] "  ","
.BI "struct device *alloc_devs[] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vq" 12
vb2_queue ptr
.IP "nbuffers" 12
ptr to number of buffers requested by application
.IP "nplanes" 12
: contains number of distinct video planes needed to hold a frame
.IP "sizes" 12
contains the size (in bytes) of each plane.
.IP "alloc_devs" 12
ptr to allocation context
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This callback function is called when \fBreqbuf\fP is called to adjust
the buffer count and buffer size
